I applied for this year&#8217;s TGO Challenge but was put on the standby list at number 37. Today I was offered a place which I gratefully accepted. Being an efficient chap, accommodation and travel to Scotland has all been booked. I&#8217;ve started my training too, although I actually feel reasonably fit. I&#8217;ve already sorted out my route which will be Plockton to Stonehaven. It&#8217;s a bit more ambitious than my previous Challenges but should be achievable if the weather plays ball. I&#8217;ll fill in some details in a while.&nbsp;</p><br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12073/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12073/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="https://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=blogpackinglight.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2188128&#038;post=12073&#038;subd=blogpackinglight&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />